-- MOVES- BGC Partners, FINRA, Jefferies
-- 
-- Fri Oct 31, 2014 06:03AM EDT
-- None



Oct 31 (Reuters) - The following financial services industry appointments were announced on Friday. To inform us of other job changes, email moves@thomsonreuters.com.

BGC PARTNERS INC <BGCP.O>  The interdealer broker said it appointed James Cawley as chief executive officer of its swap execution facility subsidiary, BGC Derivative Markets LP. [ID:nL4N0SQ65J]  FINRA  Wall Street's industry-funded watchdog on Thursday named a long-time official, Richard Berry, as the new head of its securities arbitration unit. Berry will replace the head of FINRA's arbitration unit, Linda Fienberg, who retires at the end of November after 18 years in her current job. [ID:nL1N0SP3AW]  JEFFERIES GROUP LLC [JGLL.UL]